'''Hans Vanaken''' (born 24 August 1992) is a Belgian professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as an [[attacking midfielder]] for [[Belgian Pro League]] club [[Club Brugge KV|Club Brugge]] and the [[Belgium national football team|Belgium national team]].

==Club career==
===Early career===
Vanaken began his career at the youth team of [[Lommel United]] before leaving the club to join the [[PSV Eindhoven]] academy in 2002 when the former declared bankruptcy.<ref name="ClubBruggeProfile" /> He returned to a revamped Lommel in 2008 and made his senior debut for the club in the [[Belgian Second Division]] in 2010.<ref name="ClubBruggeProfile" /> He caught the eye of a number of top division clubs after a string of standout performances for Lommel and joined [[K.S.C. Lokeren Oost-Vlaanderen|Lokeren]] in 2013.<ref name="ClubBruggeProfile" />

He made top flight debut for Lokeren on 28 July 2013, when he scored two goals in a 3–2 win against defending champions [[R.S.C. Anderlecht|Anderlecht]].<ref name="ClubBruggeProfile" /> Vanaken was instrumental in Lokeren's run to the [[2014 Belgian Cup Final|final]] of the [[2013–14 Belgian Cup]], playing in six of their seven matches and scoring one goal as his side edged out [[S.V. Zulte Waregem|Zulte Waregem]] for the title.<ref name="soccerway" /> Vanaken further excelled in his second season in the top flight, scoring eight league goals and finishing third in the voting for the [[Belgian Golden Shoe]] award.<ref name="Medical" />

===Club Brugge===
It was announced in May 2015 that Lokeren had reached an agreement with Club Brugge over the transfer of Vanaken to the latter with the player signing a five-year deal subject to a medical.<ref name="Medical">{{cite web|url=https://www.clubbrugge.be/en/news/club-brugge-reached-agreement-principle-land-hans-vanaken|title=Club Brugge reached an agreement in principle to land Hans Vanaken|website=Club Brugge|date=29 May 2015|access-date=27 January 2020}}</ref><ref name="NewContract">{{cite web|url=https://www.clubbrugge.be/en/news/prolonged-contract-hans-vanaken|title=Prolonged contract for Hans Vanaken!|website=Club Brugge|date=9 August 2019|access-date=26 January 2020}}</ref> His maiden season at Club Brugge came with a spot in the starting line-up, where he proved instrumental in helping the club lift their 14th league championship.<ref name="ClubBruggeProfile">{{cite web|url=https://www.clubbrugge.be/en/hans-vanaken#bio|title=Hans Vanaken Profile|website=Club Brugge|date=10 July 2017|access-date=26 January 2020}}</ref>

In 2018, Vanaken scored 21 goals and provided a further 21 assists as he helped his team to its 15th league title and the Belgian Supercup. On 16 January 2019, Vanaken won the [[Belgian Golden Shoe]] award after having won the [[Belgian professional football awards|Belgian Professional Footballer of the Year award]] in May 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.clubbrugge.be/en/news/golden-boot-goes-hans-vanaken|title=Golden Boot goes to Hans Vanaken!|website=Club Brugge|date=16 January 2019|access-date=26 January 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.clubbrugge.be/en/news/club-plunders-player-year-awards|title=Club plunders Player of the Year Awards|website=Club Brugge|date=14 May 2018|access-date=26 January 2020}}</ref>

Vanaken signed a new contract with Brugge on 9 August 2019, tying him to the club until 2024.<ref name="NewContract" />

On 11 December 2019, Vanaken scored Brugge's equalizing goal in their [[2019–20 UEFA Champions League|Champions League]] home match against Spanish club [[Real Madrid]]; but Brugge would eventually fall to a 3–1 defeat and be parachuted into the [[2019–20 UEFA Europa League knockout phase|UEFA Europa League]] Round of 32.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://bleacherreport.com/articles/2866545-rodrygo-real-madrid-beat-club-brugge-3-1-in-champions-league|title=Rodrygo, Real Madrid Beat Club Brugge 3-1 in Champions League|website=Bleacher Report|date=11 December 2019|access-date=26 January 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/50749103|title=Real Madrid's two Brazilian teenagers scored as they beat Club Bruges in a Champions League dead rubber match.|website=BBC|date=11 December 2019|access-date=26 January 2020}}</ref>
[[File:FC_Salzburg_vs._Club_Brügge_(Euroleague_Sechzehntelfinale)_17.jpg|thumb|260px|Vanaken with [[Club Brugge KV|Club Brugge]] against [[FC Red Bull Salzburg|Red Bull Salzburg]] in the [[2018–19 UEFA Europa League|2018–19 Europa League]]]]
On 15 January 2020, Vanaken became the first player since [[Jan Ceulemans]] in 1986 to win back-to-back Belgian Golden Shoe awards. Vanaken won the award on the back of 20 goals and 7 assists during 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.clubbrugge.be/en/news/second-golden-boot-hans-vanaken|title=A second Golden Boot for Hans Vanaken!|website=Club Brugge|date=15 January 2020|access-date=26 January 2020}}</ref> Club Brugge would win their third title in five seasons when the 2019-20 campaign was halted in March due to the [[COVID-19 pandemic]], with one round to go in the regular season. The play-offs were cancelled, and the club were crowned champions by virtue of being top.

On 20 May 2021, Vanaken scored twice as Brugge drew 3–3 with [[R.S.C. Anderlecht–Club Brugge KV rivalry|rivals]] [[R.S.C. Anderlecht|Anderlecht]] to retain the [[2020–21 Belgian First Division A|Belgian First Division A]] title, winning it for the fourth time in six years and 17th time overall.<ref name=clinch /> It was the first time since 1973 that Club Brugge had been crowned champions at Anderlecht's ground and the first time since 1976–77 and 1977–78 that Brugge had won back-to-back league titles.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/sports/soccer/2021/05/21/club-brugge-wins-back-to-back-belgian-titles/44220377/|title=Club Brugge wins back-to-back Belgian titles|website=USA Today|date=21 May 2021|accessdate=20 August 2021}}</ref>

Vanaken went on to help inspire Club to a third successive title in 2022, their first three-in-a-row since the 1970s, as they overhauled long-time leaders [[Union Saint-Gilloise]] in the play-offs, something that would happen again for Club's next title in [[2023-24 Belgian Pro League|2023-24]]. On 6 November 2024, Vanaken scored the winning goal from the penalty spot in a 1-0 win over [[Aston Villa F.C.|Aston Villa]] in the [[UEFA Champions League]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=UEFA.com |title=Club Brugge vs Aston Villa: UEFA Champions League 2024/25 League phase |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/match/2041983--club-brugge-vs-aston-villa/ |access-date=2024-11-07 |website=[[UEFA]] |language=en}}</ref>

Vanaken won his third golden shoe in February 2025, which brought him level with [[Jan Ceulemans]] and [[Wilfried Van Moer|Wilfried van Moer]]. Only [[Paul Van Himst|Paul van Himst]] has won the award more times (4 times).<ref>{{Cite web |date=4 February 2025 |title=Hans Vanaken wint derde Gouden Schoen |trans-title=Hans Vanaken wins third Golden Shoe |url=https://www.clubbrugge.be/nl/news/hans-vanaken-wint-derde-gouden-schoen |website=clubbrugge.be |language=nl}}</ref>

==International career==
Vanaken made his debut for the [[Belgium national football team|Belgium national team]] on 7 September 2018, replacing [[Eden Hazard]] in a 4–0 victory against [[Scotland national football team|Scotland]] at [[Hampden Park]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.skysports.com/football/scotland-vs-belgium/report/388918|title=Scotland 0-4 Belgium: Romelu Lukaku and Eden Hazard score|website=Sky Sports|date=7 September 2018|access-date=26 January 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/29908/11494219/timothy-castagne-hans-vanaken-leandro-trossard-birger-verstraete-who-are-belgiums-newcomers|title=Timothy Castagne, Hans Vanaken, Leandro Trossard, Birger Verstraete: Who are Belgium's newcomers?|website=Sky Sports|date=9 September 2018|access-date=26 January 2020}}</ref>

He scored his first two goals for Belgium on 30 March 2021, coming in an 8–0 win over [[Belarus national football team|Belarus]] in [[2022 FIFA World Cup qualification – UEFA Group E|qualifying]] for the 2022 FIFA World Cup.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/report?gameId=590381|title=Belgium rout of Belarus puts reserves in the spotlight|website=ESPN|date=30 March 2021}}</ref>

On 17 May 2021, Vanaken was one of two Belgium-based players to be selected for the final 26-man squad for the [[UEFA Euro 2020]], along with club teammate [[Simon Mignolet]].<ref name="Red Devils Squad">{{cite news |url=https://www.rbfa.be/en/news/selection-red-devils-euro-2020-has-been-announced |title=Selection of the Red Devils for EURO 2020 has been announced |work=[[Royal Belgian Football Association]] |date=17 May 2021 |access-date=17 May 2021}}</ref>

== Style of play ==
Standing at 1.95m tall, Vanaken is an imposing presence on the pitch. Praised for his vision and intelligence, he is a ball-retaining midfielder who can score, too. [[Pep Guardiola]], [[Vincent Kompany]], and [[Hansi Flick]] have all described Vanaken as a great player. Former Belgian international, Radja Nainggolan has called Vanaken "The most intelligent player he has ever seen on the Belgian fields".<ref>{{Cite web |last=Beeckman |first=Yanko |date=2025-11-05 |title=Na Pep Guardiola en Vincent Kompany nu ook Barcelona-trainer Hansi Flick: waarom Europese topcoaches in zwijm vallen voor Hans Vanaken |url=https://www.hln.be/club-brugge/na-pep-guardiola-en-vincent-kompany-nu-ook-barcelona-trainer-hansi-flick-waarom-europese-topcoaches-in-zwijm-vallen-voor-hans-vanaken~a8ba2c9c/ |access-date=2025-11-15 |website=HLN |language=nl}}</ref>

Vanaken also has great passing ability. He is renowned for his ability to make passes under high pressure. His combination of vision, intelligence and a "wand of a left foot", make of Vanaken a key player for Club Brugge. He is the orchestrator of the team, often dictating the pace.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Brisart |first=Axel |date=2025-01-29 |title=Guardiola heeft gelijk: dit is waarom Hans Vanaken zo'n uitzonderlijk goeie speler is |url=https://www.hln.be/champions-league/guardiola-heeft-gelijk-dit-is-waarom-hans-vanaken-zo-n-uitzonderlijk-goeie-speler-is~a5c550c7/ |access-date=2025-11-15 |website=HLN |language=nl}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=MacKichan |first=Calum |date=2021-01-28 |title=Hans Vanaken: The Belgian Star Helping Club Brugge Dominate The Pro League |url=https://worldfootballindex.com/2021/01/hans-vanaken-the-belgian-star-helping-club-brugge-dominate-the-pro-league/ |access-date=2025-11-15 |website=World Football Index |language=en-US}}</ref>

